MODULE: pipeline-infra
FILES: 8
RESPONSIBILITY: Pipeline orchestration infrastructure, config loading, script command mapping, lock/state coordination, and CLI entry abstraction
KEY_FILES:
- src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js: env+argv parsing and validated infra config object
- src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js: pipeline action to shell command mapping and process execution normalization
- src/pipeline-infra/cli-entry.js: reusable Node CLI wrapper for infra scripts
- src/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.js: lock acquisition/release and contention safety
- src/pipeline-infra/state-manager.js: daemon/state/current-session/last-result persistence
- src/pipeline-infra/path-policy.js: deterministic file and directory path conventions
- src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js: infra-specific error taxonomy and exit codes
- src/pipeline-infra/index.js: central export surface for infra module
INTERFACES:
- loadPipelineInfraConfig(input?): PipelineInfraConfig
- loadAndValidateConfig(input?): ConfigValidationResult
- buildPipelineCommand(req, config): {command,args}
- executePipelineCommand(req): Promise<PipelineResult>
- createCliEntry(options): CliEntryContext
- createLockManager(config?): LockManager
- createStateManager(config?): StateManager
DEPENDENCIES:
- node:child_process/fs/path: shell process launch and state filesystem access
- dev-pipeline shell scripts: run/status/stop/logs/retry/reset command backends
- pino: CLI logging in infra entry wrapper
UPDATED: 2026-03-19